<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-694-220  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 694 220.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  July 23 1990 v7 n28 p3(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fourth-generation language from Progress accesses Rdb, Oracle, RMSdatabases. (Progress Software Corp.) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Progress Software Corp's Progress 6.0 ranges in price from $1,050and $190,000 and gives users the ability to access and update datain Rdb and Oracle RDBMSes as well as RMS files.andP;  The new softwaresupports X windows and allows users to choose from a variety ofX-window managers including Open Look, Motif or DEC-windows.andP;  Adynamic SQL interface enables developers of tools such asspreadsheets or CASE products to link these tools to Progress.andP;  Aread-only database support, on-line backup capabilities, anincrease in the number of users per database and a DOS memorysaver are some of the other features of Progress 6.0 The softwareis available now for VMS systems, Sun workstations, NCR Towers andHewlett-Packard's 9000 series.andP;  Version 6.0 will be available forother hardware platforms later in 1990.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Progress Software Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Progress 6.0 (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Fourth-Generation LanguagesProduct IntroductionDistributed Data Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Fourth-generation language from Progress accesses Rdb, Oracle, RMS databasesandM;BEDFORD, Mass.andP;  -- Progress Software this week will release version 6.0 ofits RDBMS and fourth-generation language, which will give users the abilityto access and update data in Rdb and Oracle RDBMSes as well as RMS files,company officials said.andM;&quot;Users have data scattered all through their organizations on differentplatforms and different databases and they want to be able to pull ittogether.andP;  That's what this version lets you do,&quot; said Chip Ziering, ProgressSoftware's co-founder and vice president of development.andM;To provide distributed database access, Progress routes client requests forparticular information to a database switch.andP;  The switch then determineswhere the information is located and goes to a database gateway thattranslates the request to get the information from the database.andM;If the information is not stored locally, the request is passed to acommunications switch, which sends the message across the network to theremote database gateway.andP;  The gateway then makes the translation to retrievethe data, wherever it is located.andM;&quot;This release lets users create gateways to different databases,&quot; Zieringsaid.andP;  &quot;There's a key difference in our approach: While some vendors say,'You can have a distributed database as long as your data is located in ourdatabase,' we don't care where the data is,&quot; he said.andM;&quot;We don't want to lock you into a database.andP;  This is an emancipationproclamation,&quot; Ziering added.andM;The enhanced Progress RDBMS includes a two-phase commit architecture thatprovides data integrity when users update information across differentdatabases.andM;Version 6.0 also supports X windows, allowing users to choose from a varietyof X-window managers, including Open Look, Motif or DEC-windows, officialssaid.andM;A dynamic SQL interface enables developers of tools such as spreadsheets orCASE products to link these tools to Progress, according to the officials.andM;Other features of Progress version 6.0 include read-only database support,on-line backup capabilities, an increase in the number of users per databaseand a DOS memory saver.andM;Prices for Progress version 6.0 range from $1,050 to $190,000 for anapplication development copy.andP;  It is available now for VMS systems, Sunworkstations, NCR Towers and Hewlett-Packard's 9000 series.andM;Version 6.0 will be available on other hardware platforms later this year,including Ultrix, officials said.andM;Support for Oracle and RMS files is available now, and Rdb support is slatedto be available in the fall, company officials said.andM;Progress Software Corp. is located at 5 Oak Park, Bedford, MA 01730, (617)275-4500.andO;</TEXT></DOC>